  "commentary": "With SPX at 7114.17 sitting right at the max negative gamma strike of 7115, dealers are currently in aggressive buying mode to hedge their short gamma exposure, which is amplifying the recent upside momentum (3.9% in 5 minutes). The strong positive gamma wall at 7150 (+6722.2M) should act as initial resistance where dealer selling pressure intensifies, followed by the major 7200 level (+8298.0M) which represents the primary upside magnet where maximum dealer selling occurs. Given the PIN regime and thick positive gamma walls above, expect deceleration as price approaches 7150-7200, with dealers providing natural resistance through their hedging flows.\n\nBottom line: expect the rally to slow as SPX approaches 7150, with heavy resistance at 7200.",
